comments.comment:
Koyanskaya of Dark... The other half of Koyanskaya, which split from her during the sealing of Lostbelt: Beast IV. She has become even more wicked than when she was pretending to be a Disciple of the Foreign God. This half is the Koyanskaya who mocks and abuses Humanity.

She is Tamamo-no-Mae absent any intent to become a good wife (er, let's just put aside the question of whether you can call yourself Tamamo-no-Mae when you have no intention of being a good wife...). She is a destroyer, and her aspect as an evil spirit (a naturally occurring spirit) is at the fore.

Height/Weight: 168cm, 55kg
Origin: Fate/Grand Order
Region: Russia
Alignment: Chaotic-Evil
Gender: Female
"Do you need someone to manage obstinate creatures? Someone to raise creatures that quickly give in to temptation? Someone to train creatures? Then you've come to the right woman, for I am the Beast of Affection♡"

A bewitching, beautiful woman who believes in strict, dominant wildness over all else, and who likes nothing more than to cruelly toy with humans. She considers strong beings her enemy (and loves to turn them into pitiful weaklings by defeating them) and controls those who are already weak with love and affection. Truly the position one would expect the undisputed queen of beasts to take.

Despite being both beautiful and cruel, she does not consider affairs of the heart to be a waste of time. As she puts it, her wild nature is all the more reason to cherish love (that is to say, her intuition).

Although inherently ruthless and cold-blooded, she enjoys presenting herself as a reasonable, highly capable woman. While she does enjoy tormenting the weak, it's only because her bestial "law of the jungle" instincts are so prominent.
Even when forcing the weak to submit to her completely and utterly, she never forgets to be playful.

"It would just look silly of me if I were to get too worked up about eradicating humanity, right? So if I'm going to crush them anyway, I'm going to make sure I enjoy myself. That's right. I'm going to kill every last one of you humans as part of a game♡"

This fixation of hers to enjoy herself in everything she does mean that her attacks on humanity end up being highly serpentine. Despite coming up with all sorts of ways to oppress humanity, in the end, she decided that being kept like pets by an all-powerful champion would make humans happiest and chose to evolve into the Goddess of Taming, a being eminently well-suited for putting the screws on all of humanity.

Personality (3rd Spirit Origin)
Raiten Nikkou Honosumeraginohime-no-kami.
Thundering Light of Heaven - Fire Emperor Goddess.
As a god of nature, she speaks and acts very differently from the usual Koyanskaya...but deep down, she's still the same as ever. Well, I guess you could say she's a little more serene than usual, thanks to her Spirit Origin being less well-defined as a result of its massive scale.

Although she is a cruel and cold-blooded ruler, she is also a god who cares a great deal about wildness and generally tends to favor individual feelings.

In this form, she has toned down her typical secretary speak for more of a straightforward manner of speech befitting a primitive beast.
While only reading her lines may give the impression that she's a combination of Tamamo-no-Mae and Tamamo Cat, be aware that her elegance and stubbornness are still pure Koyanskaya.

Customer-Focused Attitude
As a human lover, Koyanskaya would never ignore or destroy a client. It's just that, as a result of Koyanskaya following her instincts for love and devoting herself to serving her client's needs, the client simply ends up forgetting their human self.

Although she also considers the Master of Chaldea a target for subjugation, she also hasn't forgotten the debt she owes for the help she herself received. An animal doesn't change its principles regardless of who it's dealing with, after all.
And so, while she would never cooperate with Chaldea (that is, humanity) she is willing to cooperate with the Master of Chaldea as a Servant.
Of course, should that Master die, she will either vanish or go right back to being an enemy of humankind.

NFF Services: EX
An original skill Koyanskaya devised to try and turn herself into the new Golden White Face. This Authority lets her use inhuman beings whose very existence was deemed intolerable by Proper Human History as extensions of her own body, making it a great fit for the next generation of a great and dangerous god.
...Or at least, that's how she likes to put it, but basically, it's just familiar creation. Koyanskaya does this by absorbing any creature with body hair into her tail's library, thereby enabling her to generate and command them as new familiars.
Just as the nine-tailed fox is the manager of pipe foxes, Koyanskaya's goal was to become the queen of all the various monstrosities that could only exist in Lostbelts.

Entity of the Outer Realm: C
This Beast IV, who first came about when a meteorite crashed to Earth, possessed the Authority to connect space to the sector of the universe that served as her origin point, which in turn led to Koyanskaya possessing this skill. It is very different from similar skills possessed by Foreigners who came to Earth from an outer universe.

Dominator Fox: A
This skill endows Koyanskaya with the Authority to tame all manner of animals (including humans) by making even better use of a system designed for domination...or so she likes to claim. In reality, it's all just her personal taste and instincts. One could also say this is a form of management-based domination.

Massacring Beasts: A
A variation on Tamamo Vitch Koyanskaya's Massacring Technique.
Essentially, a method for, well, massacring things by controlling animals. Koyanskaya can use this to completely control any animal with body hair, be it a Demonic Beast, Phantasmal, or even a Divine Beast, which she then mercilessly exploits in order to use them as perfect weapons. That being said, she is still unable to fully control ultra-powerful Divine Beasts, so the most she can do with them is boost their already considerable strength.

『Tunguska Nine Drive』
Rank: C
NP Type: Anti-World
Range: 1 - 9999
Target: One City

Raiten Nikkou - Fiery Starfall, Descending Calamity
A huge attack in which Koyanskaya absorbs every monstrosity under her command into her body, transforming herself into an enormous creature. She then brings her enormous mass crashing down to the ground like the meteorite that exploded over Tunguska, obliterating every enemy in her path. Incidentally, the Tunguska meteorite is believed to have weighed over 100,000 tons.

Back in the Chinese Lostbelt, Qin Shi Huang roughly estimated that Koyanskaya's Spirit Origin also weighed around 100,000 tons, and had most likely figured out her true identity at the time. No wonder their empire lasted for so long.

Goddess Morph (Beast): B
The Morph skill taken to its highest level.
Transforms the field into Shang Hell, an environment where humans lose all reason, devolve into beasts, and undergo intense suffering.
A recreation of the "Lake of Wine and Forest of Meat" debauchery that is said to have been King Zhou of Shang's spiritual downfall.
This skill may or may not lay bare the various crimes of Tamamo-no-Mae, the original Koyanskaya.

A Beast is a kind of evil created by the sins that arise as a result of humanity's development, and Koyanskaya was one of the candidates to become Beast IV.
This Koyanskaya had a choice to become either a being persecuted by humanity, or a being humanity used to persecute others. She chose the former, thereby becoming a Demon God that commands all manner of inhuman beasts.

Koyanskaya possesses both the right to lead all of the beasts who were born in the biosphere of humanity (including fictional creatures), and the Authority to use this ability to its maximum potential.

Unlike Koyanskaya of Light, Koyanskaya of Dark loves humans (specifically, she loves keeping them like pets, tormenting them, and snacking on them) and therefore has no intention of eradicating humanity. If anything, she wants to increase their numbers even more, so that she'll have even more of them to do with as she likes.

Koyanskaya is the collective resentment animals hold towards humans made into an arbiter. But despite being a living means for the natural world to extract revenge, she also possesses frightening flexibility to interpret things in a way that suits her personal sensibilities. Maybe it's because she's based off of Tamamo-no-Mae?

"Really, when you get right down to it, humans are just another type of animal, don't you think?"

And while Koyanskaya of Dark and Koyanskaya of Light are diametrically opposed in many ways, there is one thing they have in common. Despite being enemies of humanity, and having no desire to be a good wife, they will never be fully rid of Tamamo-no-Mae's inherent inclination to serve others.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 1
voiceLines.subtitle: I may have answered your summons, but know that I am a contractor. Please do not forget that I am simply a woman who is on a business trip, dispatched by NFF Services. My plan to create my own primate realm might have fallen through, but my policy remains unchanged.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 2
voiceLines.subtitle: I have come into existence as an Evil of Humanity. I treat humanity as prey, scouting and managing them. That is how I dominate them. Well, to put it simply, I make them my playthings.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
Chaldea and NFF... Working two jobs at the same time is certainly exhausting. In times like this, troubling my employer with unreasonable arguments is my way to relieve stress.
(Sigh)
Master, you always receive me with a smile, and so I can only talk about pleasantries. But please do not get the wrong idea. Think of this like a beautiful secretary who, exhausted from her daily duties, finds comfort from her pet.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
This may be late to mention, but the working conditions in Chaldea are terrible. You work full-time, yet are always on standby for emergencies. 
Working conditions like that...
...are the kind of hard work I love♡
Considering there has not been any strikes, I have never seen such a wonderful corporate drone environment.
Master, would you seriously consider getting headhunted by my company?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 5
voiceLines.subtitle:
So you do not want to be hired by me...
You're saying headhunting is no good?
But you want me to try asking again after the world turns peaceful and you search for a new job after you go back to your hometown?
Pffft. Ahaha. Hahahaha!
Apologies. I couldn't help myself because you said it so seriously! Very well. Then I shall lend you my hand so that day will come soon.
After all, I am a competent and beautiful secretary. I shall prepare a road map to world peace.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 1
voiceLines.subtitle: It is time to work. I will not tolerate tardiness, Master.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
I do not define a Master and Servant relationship just by power alone, because that would simply be one-sided.
What's written in the contract is everything to me...including the rules that bind me, as well.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
My relationship with you, Master?
You are obviously my employee, and therefore, you are someone that I must protect, manage, and plunder.
Hm? I thought that was explicitly stated in our contract from the very beginning.

voiceLines.name: Likes
voiceLines.subtitle: I like all sorts of pure and innocent animals. This includes beasts that prioritize profits for themselves. Hehe. Have you ever heard of the term "economic animals"?

voiceLines.name: Dislikes
voiceLines.subtitle: I dislike lazy animals. Please always keep in mind that I personally reeducate animals who forget to work and serve others♡

voiceLines.name: About the Holy Grail
voiceLines.subtitle:
Holy Grail?
I'm sure the Light part of me dislikes it, but the Dark me acknowledges it. After all, everyone should be rewarded for their work. Anybody who is willing to die for me should be rewarded with something like that, at the very least. Do you not agree?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 7
voiceLines.subtitle:
Lobo the Wolf King...
It pains me to see his entire being engulfed in revenge against humans...
But I do not pity him. Rage is his pride, his everything. I pray that his hatred continues until the world ends.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 8
voiceLines.subtitle:
Ehehehe.
I once stated that I am able to unconditionally control all furry animals, but I will take that statement back.
Tamamo Cat is someone I cannot control.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 9
voiceLines.subtitle:
An ideology that values mankind only as a labor force...
A collection of merciless torture tools...
I do say Mecha Eli-chan Mk.II is my type, but it's a shame that metallic weapons are more in the taste of my Light side. Mecha Eli-chan is a gem that is beyond my reach.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 10
voiceLines.subtitle: I had no idea you were here too, Nikitich. You certainly formed a wonderful contract, Master. If you ever dare betray her trust, be warned that you will see my true nature at that time.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 11
voiceLines.subtitle:
Atalante is such a darling. She is easily tricked by good people, while she never warms up to evil people...
She is truly a diamond in the rough that is worth training♡

voiceLines.name: Conversation 12
voiceLines.subtitle:
Limbo?
Hehehe. Master, please don't get the wrong idea. It's not that I like all felines...especially those that lack love.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 13
voiceLines.subtitle:
Oh, Beni!!! Mmm! (Smooch, smooch)
So earnest! So pure! So gullible! You're everything I love! You are more than welcome to build a nest using my hat! 
Oh... She ran away again... Why does Beni-Enma recoil from my embrace?
Hm? What is with your look of disapproval? Don't tell me there's something wrong with how I approach her!?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 14
voiceLines.subtitle:
Red Hare... Yes, he does have fur, but...
Since he declares himself Lu Bu, he is a part of humanity in my book.
My circus doesn't need a character for comic relief...

voiceLines.name: Conversation 15
voiceLines.subtitle: Mélusine, the dragon Albion's remains. Thanks to her, my plan was foiled. I obviously resent her, but all plans change based on circumstance. We must be flexible in the face of trouble. That's my motto.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 16
voiceLines.subtitle: Edison! A man who emits feral beauty boasting a mane of champions, combined with unparalleled industrial strength! A hideous combination like that can only mean that he's challenging me! His combination of light and dark are clearly a matter of copyright infringement, and I have no choice but to take legal action against him!

voiceLines.name: During an Event
voiceLines.subtitle:
Master, there is an event happening.
I will not allow a business opportunity to slip away.
You will not be able to return to your room until we rake in a bunch of money, so please keep that in mind♡

voiceLines.name: Birthday
voiceLines.subtitle:
It is your birthday, correct?
In the morning at 0700 hours, you will have breakfast at the NFF Royal Hotel.
At 0900 hours, you have a tour through Tamamo Vitch City.
At 1300 hours, you have an inspection at Koyanskayaland. The park naturally has been rented out for you exclusively. 
At 1800 hours, you will stroll through the Bunny Casino on the eastern coast, and upon your return to the office, you will have dinner at the top floor.
You know what comes after that...don't you? I promise you will have the best day in human history, Master♡

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_0_G010]Growth?
[id 2500900_0_G011]Thank you for investing in me.
[id 2500900_0_G012]I love you, Master.

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_0_G110]That is a wise transaction.
[id 2500900_0_G111]There is no way my company's stock price will collapse.
[id 2500900_0_G112]We shall take care even more of your assets as well as your utmost trust.

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_0_G120]Hehe. Just what part of me do you want me to improve on? 
[id 2500900_0_G121]Please tell me which body part you like.

voiceLines.name: Summon
text: Hello, this is the NFF call center♡[r]
Tamamo Vitch Koyanskaya, has taken up post after high demand.[r]
Oh? You think I am unwilling to help all of you?[r]
That is untrue. You humans are like my playthings. I will protect you at all costs.[r]
And besides...it wouldn't be a good look if I got all serious trying to annihilating humanity, now would it?

Hello, this is the NFF call center♡
Servant, Foreigner. Tamamo Vitch Koyanskaya, has taken up post after high demand.
Oh? You think I am unwilling to help all of you?
That is untrue. You humans are like my playthings. I will protect you at all costs.
And besides...it wouldn't be a good look if I got all serious trying to annihilating humanity, now would it?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
Spying is Light's job.
As Dark, my job is to manage, caretake, and train. I may be strict, but this is all in the name of love.
Would you like to experience it yourself?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
I say that I can unconditionally assimilate creatures with fur, but with enough time, even furless life-forms can also become my slav―I mean, my familiars.
Free will? Of course I'd never tamper with their wills. I just make it so that they can never disobey me.
This dazzling NFF sticker is proof that their rights and livelihood have been seized.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
I've headhunted demonic beasts unique to each of the Lostbelts, but Qin was the only place that did not have any unique demonic beasts, which was quite problematic.
Come again? What about the tanks that work for me? Well, that... I just took a liking to them...
Just look, it has a tiger design!

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
I may be saying something obvious, but I have to say you have the qualities of a guard dog, Master.
You're a hard worker, earnest, and patient. But at the same time, you have a playful nature and creative side to you.
I'm starting to think it would be a waste to have you out and about.
Would you be interested in becoming an indoor dog for the VIP room?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 5
voiceLines.subtitle:
Master♡ Here is the secondary contract for you to sign. It states that as the Master who has summoned Tamamo Vitch Koyanskaya of Dark, upon the end of your services at Chaldea, you will be transferred to NFF Services and serve the same duration as your tenure in Chaldea.
Wonderful, don't you think? You don't want to, because you'll be worked to the bone?
Oh, hahaha, obviously. But rest assured, you will be treated with care.
Come on, now you will be compelled to sign the contract... The compelling force of my whip will drive you to sign it...
Ah yes, our contract has now been established♡
Do not forget about our agreement after you leave Chaldea, okay?♡

voiceLines.name: Conversation 1
voiceLines.subtitle: It is time to work. I will not tolerate tardiness, Master.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
I do not define a Master and Servant relationship just by power alone, because that would simply be one-sided.
What's written in the contract is everything to me...including the rules that bind me, as well.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
My relationship with you, Master?
You are obviously my employee, and therefore, you are someone that I must protect, manage, and plunder.
Hm? I thought that was explicitly stated in our contract from the very beginning.

voiceLines.name: Likes
voiceLines.subtitle: I like all sorts of pure and innocent animals. This includes beasts that prioritize profits for themselves. Hehe. Have you ever heard of the term "economic animals"?

voiceLines.name: Dislikes
voiceLines.subtitle: I dislike lazy animals. Please always keep in mind that I personally reeducate animals who forget to work and serve others♡

voiceLines.name: About the Holy Grail
voiceLines.subtitle:
Holy Grail?
I'm sure the Light part of me dislikes it, but the Dark me acknowledges it. After all, everyone should be rewarded for their work. Anybody who is willing to die for me should be rewarded with something like that, at the very least. Do you not agree?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 7
voiceLines.subtitle:
Lobo the Wolf King...
It pains me to see his entire being engulfed in revenge against humans...
But I do not pity him. Rage is his pride, his everything. I pray that his hatred continues until the world ends.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 8
voiceLines.subtitle:
Ehehehe.
I once stated that I am able to unconditionally control all furry animals, but I will take that statement back.
Tamamo Cat is someone I cannot control.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 9
voiceLines.subtitle:
An ideology that values mankind only as a labor force...
A collection of merciless torture tools...
I do say Mecha Eli-chan Mk.II is my type, but it's a shame that metallic weapons are more in the taste of my Light side. Mecha Eli-chan is a gem that is beyond my reach.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 10
voiceLines.subtitle: I had no idea you were here too, Nikitich. You certainly formed a wonderful contract, Master. If you ever dare betray her trust, be warned that you will see my true nature at that time.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 11
voiceLines.subtitle:
Atalante is such a darling. She is easily tricked by good people, while she never warms up to evil people...
She is truly a diamond in the rough that is worth training♡

voiceLines.name: Conversation 12
voiceLines.subtitle:
Limbo?
Hehehe. Master, please don't get the wrong idea. It's not that I like all felines...especially those that lack love.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 13
voiceLines.subtitle:
Oh, Beni!!! Mmm! (Smooch, smooch)
So earnest! So pure! So gullible! You're everything I love! You are more than welcome to build a nest using my hat! 
Oh... She ran away again... Why does Beni-Enma recoil from my embrace?
Hm? What is with your look of disapproval? Don't tell me there's something wrong with how I approach her!?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 14
voiceLines.subtitle:
Red Hare... Yes, he does have fur, but...
Since he declares himself Lu Bu, he is a part of humanity in my book.
My circus doesn't need a character for comic relief...

voiceLines.name: Conversation 15
voiceLines.subtitle: Mélusine, the dragon Albion's remains. Thanks to her, my plan was foiled. I obviously resent her, but all plans change based on circumstance. We must be flexible in the face of trouble. That's my motto.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 16
voiceLines.subtitle: Edison! A man who emits feral beauty boasting a mane of champions, combined with unparalleled industrial strength! A hideous combination like that can only mean that he's challenging me! His combination of light and dark are clearly a matter of copyright infringement, and I have no choice but to take legal action against him!

voiceLines.name: During an Event
voiceLines.subtitle:
Master, there is an event happening.
I will not allow a business opportunity to slip away.
You will not be able to return to your room until we rake in a bunch of money, so please keep that in mind♡

voiceLines.name: Birthday
voiceLines.subtitle:
It is your birthday, correct?
In the morning at 0700 hours, you will have breakfast at the NFF Royal Hotel.
At 0900 hours, you have a tour through Tamamo Vitch City.
At 1300 hours, you have an inspection at Koyanskayaland. The park naturally has been rented out for you exclusively. 
At 1800 hours, you will stroll through the Bunny Casino on the eastern coast, and upon your return to the office, you will have dinner at the top floor.
You know what comes after that...don't you? I promise you will have the best day in human history, Master♡

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_1_G010]All animals are lives to be loved.
[id 2500900_1_G011]I will train them with love.
[id 2500900_1_G012]Thoroughly, that is.

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_1_G110]Hehe. My whip to tie you up has become even more pliable♡
[id 2500900_1_G111]I mean... Ahem. Let me rephrase that...
[id 2500900_1_G112]My whip to train you, that is.
[id 2500900_1_G113]T-r-a-i-n♡

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_1_G120]Do you desire an even more alluring show?
[id 2500900_1_G121]Well then, I will prepare a ticket, just for you.

voiceLines.name: Ascension 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_1_G030]My role as the face of NFF Services is put on hold for the time being. [id 2500900_1_G031]From here on out, I will serve as the ringleader of the NFF Circus.
[id 2500900_1_G032]However, I do have to warn you: [id 2500900_1_G033]my work here is not for the sake of humans, but for the animals. [id 2500900_1_G034]Please do not forget that you humans are the ones to be used as prey♡

voiceLines.name: Ascension 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_1_G020]Phew...
[id 2500900_1_G021]I seem to have Ascended without incident.
[id 2500900_1_G022]However, I am at my limit. I feel like I will burst the next time...
[id 2500900_1_G023]Do you think you can embrace my true nature and survive, Master?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
I was born out of the vindictive voices of the animals. Their cries of hatred and suffering from being abused. Their grief and compassion from loss. They remembered everything, the good and the bad.
That is why I came to be who I am. I punish humans and use them as sustenance. I forgive humans and make them my companions. My embrace of both extremes is what makes me a god of calamity.
Keep that in mind at all times.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 2
voiceLines.subtitle:
I love humans.
They are so darling when I attack them incessantly.
They are delicious when consumed.
They are interesting when raised.
I am grateful to this planet for designing a creature so worthy of protection.

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
Animals don't need love, you say? 
The more feral they are, the more they live by their instincts. Love is like lightning that drives life.
Wearing clothes and using your reasoning... Honestly, what are you humans so afraid of exposing?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
You have nothing to fear.
I am here to protect you from all calamities and hostilities. 
...Then again, I'm still a beast before I am a god, so I might want to indulge in the taste of chaos once in a while. I do hope you would be forgiving on that part.
For a deity's sake, you know?

voiceLines.name: Bond Level 5
voiceLines.subtitle:
I admit it was certainly worth turning into a Servant. I see you are a human who reveres me without fear, uses me efficiently, and provides decent offerings to me. You are undoubtedly my priest now. 
You have come to understand how beasts feel and you did not hesitate to devote yourself to them. You have managed to avoid the tragedy mentioned in the story of Gongitsune, the little fox.
All you need to do now is to strip away your virtue, or rather, your rationale, and lower yourself to a beast. This may still take a lot of work, but I'm sure the years it will take to do so will be fun.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 1
voiceLines.subtitle:
Are we going out on an expedition?
I do hope we find formidable slave candidates...

voiceLines.name: Conversation 2
voiceLines.subtitle: I simply act as I see fit. Do not think you can put a leash on me. However, I will allow you to hold onto my shimenawa, a rope that wards off evil spirits. I dare you to try to untie it. Good luck♡

voiceLines.name: Conversation 3
voiceLines.subtitle: My relationship with you, Master? You may lack experience, but I wouldn't mind having you be my voice one day. I look forward to the day when we can communicate and read each other's minds♡

voiceLines.name: Likes
voiceLines.subtitle:
What I like?
Hehehe. You know exactly what I like.
I love enemies who are worthy of tormenting, and the enemies that have already been tormented.

voiceLines.name: Dislikes
voiceLines.subtitle:
What I dislike...
I do not like weapons made of iron.
After all, that's more my other half's forte, whom I tried to detach myself from.

voiceLines.name: About the Holy Grail
voiceLines.subtitle:
A Holy Grail that grants wishes...
Considering that a good number of them exist shows how pitiful humans are.
If you cannot live your day-to-day life, you might as well hand it over to me. I will use it to grow more powerful and I will suppress the humans.
What better use could there be for it?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 17
voiceLines.subtitle:
Tamamo no Mae...a Divine Spirit calling herself a partial reincarnation of the sun...
We were born from the vestiges she left behind, and awakened with a different purpose. We are eighty percent not the same person, or rather, not the same Tamamo. Specifically, I am the next generation Tamamo-no-Mae. If she is Mikon 1.0, then I am Mikon 2.5.
I am a Mikon with functions updated for the current age♡

voiceLines.name: Conversation 18
voiceLines.subtitle:
That scent...it's Taigong Wang!
Unforgiveable! I can overlook all other beast hunters as mere savages, but I absolutely refuse to forgive that man!
I intend to pluck his unnecessarily long limbs from his body and mount his handsome head on the finest grave!

voiceLines.name: Conversation 19
voiceLines.subtitle:
Many humans may have reached godhood, but I never imagined I would ever meet a human who surpassed gods.
Actually, hold on a minute...
Her mental structure can't even be expressed in hyper dimensions! What the heck...she's making an entire universe in her stomach!?

voiceLines.name: Conversation 20
voiceLines.subtitle:
Ashtart, a primordial goddess from a distant future and a distant past. If time is expressed as a scroll, she is a being who came about from an unfurled scroll that happened to fold back over on itself.
I would love to make her temple mine one day.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 21
voiceLines.subtitle:
A huntress of the wicked...XX?
But no matter how I look at her, she's just some exhausted public servant.
Eh? Hold on. What is that spear she has in her hand?
Is that ritualistic equipment on par with Amenonuboko? That's a Space Amenonuboko? All the wicked in the world need to be eradicated?
...Master, I think there is something wrong with your Chaldea.

voiceLines.name: Conversation 22
voiceLines.subtitle:
Goddess Artemis...she is certainly a Divine Spirit to be reckoned with.
Her beauty and her smile are hard to compete against, and she makes full use of her powerful divine retribution. On top of it all, she carries around a lovely animal...
Hehehe...I feel our interests align.
I wonder if I should borrow her bear one day...

voiceLines.name: Conversation 22
voiceLines.subtitle: Kama, the god of love. She, like me, battled Chaldea as an immature Beast and was defeated. Normally I should consider her my compatriot, but it appears we do not get along well. I suppose this is the phenomenon of disliking people similar to oneself.

voiceLines.name: During an Event
voiceLines.subtitle:
Is there some sort of festival going on?
It does not seem to concern me, but I do not mind going, since I shall subjugate every single stall that catches my eyes.

voiceLines.name: Birthday
voiceLines.subtitle:
Happy birthday.
As I am a god, I am more than forthcoming to celebrate. Here, take this.
It is an unbreakable ring made from a mineral that, in recent days, is called lonsdaleite.
I suggest you put it around your neck.
You're saying it's too big to fit around a finger? It's not something that should be put around one's neck?
Oh, my mistake. I am a god, after all. I must have made it with the wrong proportions♡

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_2_G010]A tribute?
[id 2500900_2_G011]Hehehe, do as you see fit.

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_G110]Good intentions like this are what I expect from my devotee. [id 2500900_2_G111]Here, take this auspicious talisman as a reward. [id 2500900_2_G112]Stick it on your forehead when you sleep and it will keep you cool.

voiceLines.name: Level up
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_2_G120]Wonderful, wonderful.
[id 2500900_2_G121]The celestial fox is the law of the skies.
[id 2500900_2_G122]I shall show you that by engulfing the sun one of these days.

voiceLines.name: Ascension 3
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_2_G040]I became a god while a beast, then turned into a god for the beasts.
[id 2500900_2_G041]The ill-omened star that does not build nations, but destroys them.
[id 2500900_2_G042,2500900_2_G043]I have descended as the goddess of thunder and flame, Honosumeraginohime-no-kami.
[id 2500900_2_G044]Come...I will trample it all, and everything will become part of my kin!

voiceLines.name: Ascension 4
voiceLines.subtitle:
[id 2500900_2_G050]You sure are a perverse person, [delay 3.6]having come this far with me even though you know I am Dark.
[id 2500900_2_G051]Well then...I will seal my Divine Spirit mode for the time being. [id 2500900_2_G052]Gods are magnanimous,  [delay 3.1]so there is no particular difference between acting in malice or goodwill. 
[id 2500900_2_G053]Yet, you will not be able to understand my true nature. [id 2500900_2_G054]As you can see, I am a woman who rules over the wild and feral.
[id 2500900_2_G055]As long as the contract between me and you is intact, [delay 2.9]you are just another animal in my eyes. [id 2500900_2_G056]It will be your choice whether to submit yourself [delay 2.9]like a bunny or continue to starve like a dog...
[id 2500900_2_G057]Whichever you choose, [delay 3.8]I will raise you into a superb beast using both sweet and heinous methods.

voiceLines.name: Battle Start 1
voiceLines.subtitle: They intend to fight me? These small fry sure have the nerve.

voiceLines.name: Battle Start 2
voiceLines.subtitle: Aren't these sacrifices too small for a god?

voiceLines.name: Battle Start 3
voiceLines.subtitle: Very well. I will deliver hair-raising carnage and tantalizing excitement.

voiceLines.name: Skill 1
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B080]How disappointing...

voiceLines.name: Skill 2
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B090]Enjoy yourselves here.

voiceLines.name: Skill 3
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B480]I shall devour them all!

voiceLines.name: Command Card 1
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B180]Lap them up♡

voiceLines.name: Command Card 2
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B190]Mock them♡

voiceLines.name: Command Card 3
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B200]Eat them clean♡

voiceLines.name: Noble Phantasm Card
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B220]You desire to end this world, do you not?

voiceLines.name: Noble Phantasm Card
voiceLines.subtitle: [id 2500900_2_B230]This way to the shelter♡

voiceLines.name: Attack 1
voiceLines.subtitle: Heaps of corpses, a river of blood.

voiceLines.name: Attack 2
